<br>
So when Brell opened, billed as an &quot;unofficial roleplaying server&quot;, that seemed like a good chance to escape and we took it. It turned out to be an excellent choice. Brell isn't as much of a RP server as I'd hoped, but still much more so than Cazic. And the server culture is much more polite and considerate than most.<br>
<br>
On Cazic I played a Ranger first, then a Shaman. Both classes were good, but on Brell I wanted to try something different. I'd been reading about Enchanters and decided to go for it, and that turned out to be the right choice too. I started as a High Elf, but the horrific overcrowding in GFay was unbearable. I went with Erudite because of the relatively poor and thus relatively uncrowded newbie zone. <br>
<br>
Now the difficulty of finding groups without resorting to pick-up groups, which I hate, is forcing me to play something else, and I've settled on a Vah Shir Shaman. I liked that class before on Cazic, so time to give it another try.  <p><font color="yellow"><B><I>Cyndassa Ebonstar</B></I>,<font color="white"><BR>
